// TinyGo on Windows/amd64 emits calls to the stack-probe routine ___chkstk_ms
// in some function prologues (e.g. engine.NewGame) but does not always supply
// the symbol, causing a link error "undefined symbol: ___chkstk_ms".
//
// TinyGo decorates C symbols on Windows with a leading underscore, so we define
// __chkstk_ms (two underscores) which becomes ___chkstk_ms (three) in the
// object file -- exactly the symbol the linker wants. The three-underscore
// variant is also defined in case the toolchain does not decorate.
void __chkstk_ms(void) {}

void ___chkstk_ms(void) {}
